Task Management App
Overview
This is a GUI-based Task Management App built using Python and the tkinter library. The app allows users to:

Add new tasks.
Delete completed or unwanted tasks.
Track and manage a list of tasks effectively.
The application features a user-friendly and aesthetically pleasing interface.

Features
Add tasks to a to-do list.
Delete tasks from the list.
Clear all tasks with a single click.
Save tasks to a file for future reference.
Load tasks from a saved file.

Installation
Ensure Python 3.x is installed on your system.
Install the required libraries (if not already installed):
bash
Copy code
pip install tk
Clone this repository or download the project files.

How to Run
Navigate to the project directory:
bash
Copy code
cd GUI_ToDo_App
Run the Python file:
bash
Copy code
python app.py

Usage
Launch the app.
Use the entry box to type your task and click "Add Task" to add it to the list.
Select a task from the list and click "Delete Task" to remove it.
Click "Save Tasks" to save the current task list to a file.
Click "Load Tasks" to load tasks from a previously saved file.
Click "Clear All Tasks" to remove all tasks from the list.

Technologies Used
Language: Python
GUI Library: tkinter

Future Improvements
Add functionality to edit tasks.
Implement priority levels for tasks.
Add a calendar view for scheduling.

